216
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,640
These people, seriously...

217
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:06,240
So how much should the stakes be?

218
00:12:08,050 --> 00:12:10,170
Manager Seong, do you want to hear a funny story?

219
00:12:10,170 --> 00:12:11,180
No.

220
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:15,180
What sound does Cha Wa Wa make when he laughs?

221
00:12:15,180 --> 00:12:17,230
Cha-Wa-Wa.

222
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:21,170
Cha-Wa-Wa.

223
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:23,730
Wait a minute.

224
00:12:23,730 --> 00:12:25,190
Let's say someone's j-walking on the street.

225
00:12:25,190 --> 00:12:27,780
"Hey, you can't j-walk!" If you say that in three letters...

226
00:12:27,780 --> 00:12:31,110
it's Cha-Wa-Wa.
(Cha=car, Wa=coming, Wa=Whoa! in Korean)

227
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:33,510
Cha-Wa-Wa.

228
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:36,660
Why don't you do some work?

229
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:38,750
