234
00:12:49,590 --> 00:12:52,940
Have a good lunch, Cha-Wa-Wa.

235
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:55,410
You!

236
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,950
I-I think she did smile a bit!

237
00:12:59,950 --> 00:13:01,940
Didn't you see it?

238
00:13:01,940 --> 00:13:04,620
How do you think I feel right now?

239
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:09,150
Cha-Wa-Wa-Wa-Wa...

240
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:11,240
Cha-Wa-Wa!

241
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:14,370
You guys should just laugh if it's funny!

242
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:19,000
Smooth sweetness spreads in my mouth.

243
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,400
The funny texture entertains both my tongue and my teeth.

244
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:26,410
I personally like the walnut pastries sold at service areas the most.

245
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,580
Walnut pastry?

246
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:31,520
- Is it called that because it's "wal"-liked by everyone?
- Ma Tan.

247
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:35,050
- What kind of food do you like?
- Not sure.

248
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:39,120
Before living alone, I usually liked to eat truffle chips.

249
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,850
Truffle chips?

250
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:46,860
Why don't you say you also ate stuff like caviar puddings?

251
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:50,460
Yes. That one pairs well with Darjeeling tea...

252
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:52,450
although not as well as foie gras ice cream.

253
00:13:52,450 --> 00:13:56,840
Ma Tan, you... must come from quite a wealthy family.

254
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,990
We're about upper-middle class.

255
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:05,490
