259
00:14:11,460 --> 00:14:13,540
We'd be spending all of our per diem allowances on him then.

260
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:16,020
If I talk to him well, we can use him for free.

261
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:18,970
It's not like he's your private driver, so how?

262
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:23,980
Yes, Secretary Kim—

263
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:28,490
I mean, Brother!

264
00:14:28,490 --> 00:14:30,950
Could you send me a driver right now?

265
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:32,030
I'm sorry, Young Boss.

266
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:36,200
Chairman told me not to give you any help until you come back to Power.

267
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:38,820
He made an earnest request.

268
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:41,040
I understand, Secretary Kim—

269
00:14:42,260 --> 00:14:45,920
I mean, Brother. I must've troubled you.

270
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,530
He said he couldn't do it for me right now.

271
00:14:49,530 --> 00:14:51,010
Also, that brother's name is Bi Seo.
(Secretary in Korean)

272
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:55,120
- Just in case you misunderstand...
- Ma Tan, you... assumed a really peculiar concept of personality.

273
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:57,040
- Sorry?
- Oh, nothing. Nothing.

274
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:59,250
You must not be in the right mind since we've been on the road since the morning.

275
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:02,680
If you're tired, just sleep like before.

276
00:15:03,620 --> 00:15:06,040
Then should I return to the backseat?

277
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:08,070
Just sleep there.

278
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:13,130
It's ticklish, right? Right? Right?

279
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:16,780
- You're holding your laugh, right?
- What are you doing?

280
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:18,680
Why aren't you laughing?

281
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:21,560
Isn't it weird to laugh when you're in pain?

282
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:23,510
I think I even got a bruise just now.

283
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:25,590
Gosh, it hurts.

284
00:15:25,590 --> 00:15:27,040
Are you not ticklish?

285
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:29,360
No. I'm not.

286
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:31,060
I'm sorry.

287
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:35,480
That's too one-dimensional.

288
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,400
Hey, this is going to work for sure. Right?

289
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,610
Wouldn't this contrarily reduce the humor when you attempt to make

290
00:15:42,610 --> 00:15:44,690
her laugh with one-dimensional stuff like this?

291
00:15:44,690 --> 00:15:46,880
It only reveals your anxious heart, Manager.

292
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:48,330
Is that so?

293
00:15:48,330 --> 00:15:51,120
Hey, how are you going to make her laugh then?

294
00:15:58,010 --> 00:15:59,880
Hey! That was mine!

295
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,430
Hey, you thief! Come here.

296
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:04,390
Hey, you thief! You said it's one-dimensional!

297
00:16:04,390 --> 00:16:06,550
You said it's one-dimensional. You said it's one-dimensional!

298
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:08,090
That's why I drew two streaks!

299
00:16:08,090 --> 00:16:10,360
Silence!

300
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,220
Are you in elementary school or something?

301
00:16:13,630 --> 00:16:16,390
Manager Seong... please laugh once.

302
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:20,270
They're wasting even more time than usual because of that rumor.

303
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:22,810
I'll even beg of you like this. Please laugh once. Look closely.

304
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:25,030
If she laughs now, it's my win.

305
00:16:25,030 --> 00:16:26,870
Come on.

306
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:30,950
It's not like I'm a genie in a bottle.

307
00:16:30,950 --> 00:16:34,090
Good results come out if you do good work...

308
00:16:34,090 --> 00:16:36,920
not from making me laugh with stupid makeup.

309
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:38,500
Manager Seong...

310
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:47,230
Even you, Executive Manager? Why?

311
00:16:47,230 --> 00:16:49,060
Sorry? What?

312
00:16:49,060 --> 00:16:50,960
I-Is there something on my face?

313
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:54,350
Gosh, I just had kimbap, so...

314
00:16:54,350 --> 00:16:56,040
I-I'm sorry. Sorry.

315
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:00,620
Wait—

316
00:17:03,310 --> 00:17:06,740
So sad... Why are you stingy, Manager Seong?

317
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:08,760
They say good fortune comes to those who laugh.

318
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:11,820
Don't you want to be fortunate? Come on and laugh now.

319
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:15,730
Manager Seong, this is an order from your superior!

320
00:17:15,730 --> 00:17:17,240
Laugh!

321
00:17:18,630 --> 00:17:20,370
I've never seen someone making others laugh that way.

322
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:21,460
Do you think your superior is laughable?

323
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,800
If you do!

324
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,340
Then you should laugh. Smile, smile.

325
00:17:25,340 --> 00:17:28,280
Like Lee Byeong Heon, you know... just a little bit.

326
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:30,480
A smile. Just a smile.

327
00:17:34,090 --> 00:17:37,830
I thought of H One Electronics as a small subcontractor because its office was

328
00:17:37,830 --> 00:17:40,140
just as big as my rental room, but I guess it wasn't.

329
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:44,050
Wow... Your rental room must be... quite large, Ma Tan. Right?

330
00:17:44,050 --> 00:17:45,930
Rental room...

331
00:17:45,930 --> 00:17:47,040
No.

332
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,730
It's just a studio.

333
00:17:48,730 --> 00:17:51,640
Studios do come pretty spacious nowadays.

334
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:53,350
Yes, they're about this big.

335
00:17:53,350 --> 00:17:56,020
It's smaller than this place.

336
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:57,310
My goodness, have you been doing well?

337
00:17:57,310 --> 00:17:58,620
Goodness, long time no see, General Manager.

338
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,930
I'm sorry to make you wait after your long trip.

339
00:18:00,930 --> 00:18:02,800
Not at all.

340
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:07,370
He's our new director who came from our HQ in Germany.

341
00:18:07,370 --> 00:18:10,650
He's going to advise you on core technology that will be used for the Gaboss Project.

342
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:12,760
- I see. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

343
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:15,710
These are the gentlemen from Gaus Electronics.

344
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:20,880
Prince?

345
00:18:22,830 --> 00:18:25,270
You're working for Gaus?
(Said in German)

346
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,360
Does he know him? I don't speak German that well.

347
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:29,150
I don't really speak German as well...

348
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:31,860
Long time no see, Zokerberg.

349
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:35,480
I'm currently working at Gaus for a reason.

350
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,850
Gaus?

351
00:18:36,850 --> 00:18:38,870
Power even acquired Gaus?

352
00:18:38,870 --> 00:18:41,260
- Power?
- Power...

353
00:18:41,260 --> 00:18:43,430
No, that's not the case.

354
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:45,890
These people don't know about it...

355
00:18:45,890 --> 00:18:49,010
so please keep my background a secret.

356
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:50,380
Seriously?

357
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:53,190
Are you filming "Undercover Boss" or something?

358
00:18:53,190 --> 00:18:54,660
- Boss?
- Boss...

359
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:57,610
This is interesting. Where is the camera?

360
00:18:57,610 --> 00:18:58,820
- Cameras?
- The cameras are...

361
00:18:58,820 --> 00:19:00,030
This is not Candid Camera.

362
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:01,610
I'm seriously a new employee at Gaus.

363
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:03,990
Anyway, just pretend that you don't know me.

364
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:06,370
Okay. I'll make sure.

365
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:10,600
Well, the thing is... he's a friend who I met on the trip.

366
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:13,020
I was just too glad to see him in a place like this.

367
00:19:13,020 --> 00:19:16,090
- I see... a trip.
- I don't know this person.

368
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,220
You don't know?

369
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:20,630
I thought you two just had a conversation...

370
00:19:20,630 --> 00:19:24,320
He speaks some nonsense German, but... this is my first time seeing this person.

371
00:19:25,150 --> 00:19:28,640
But why did he bother doing that... at this meeting?

372
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:35,640
I apologize. My subordinate... likes to do things for show a bit...

373
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:37,270
Please excuse him.

374
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:42,000
Okay.

375
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,760
Good day.

376
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,880
- We'll be going now then.
- Okay, please take care.

377
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:50,040
- Please take care.
- Yes, thank you.

378
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,720
It was a good try.

379
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:59,900
You want to be noticed and get recognized even a little. Right?

380
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:02,340
I was also the same when I was new. It's only natural.

381
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:05,040
- What do you mean—
- However, Ma Tan...

382
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,530
I'm not your rival.

383
00:20:06,530 --> 00:20:08,980
I'm just a good senior and friendly brother.

384
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:12,330
So you don't have to pretend to be rich, strong, or different

385
00:20:12,330 --> 00:20:15,270
from others in front of me at least. You understand?

386
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:21,400
We're done with everything for the day. Let's go and get some rest.

387
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,120
Here.

388
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:25,890
Wait! Do you know of PW Juliette Hotel?

389
00:20:25,890 --> 00:20:29,010
Are you talking about the PW Hotel that's a subsidiary of Power?

390
00:20:29,010 --> 00:20:30,440
Whoa... You do know, huh?

391
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:34,490
That place is so expensive in Seoul, but the price was all right in this region.

392
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:37,960
[PVV Juliette Hotel]

393
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,400
[PVV Juliette Hotel]

394
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:43,480
There was a reason why the price was all right.

395
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:46,880
It was PVV, not PW.

396
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,460
The "W" did look a bit long.

397
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:54,590
Still, what's a business trip without sleeping at places like these?

398
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:56,880
- Let's go in.
- You should sleep here alone comfortably.

399
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,770
I'll go somewhere else nearby because someone I know

400
00:20:58,770 --> 00:21:00,090
opened up a hotel around here.

401
00:21:00,090 --> 00:21:01,670
Ma Tan, you... again!

402
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:03,780
I told you this already. You don't have to pretend in front of me!

403
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:05,230
Gosh, let's go in.

404
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:07,000
- I really have a nearby—
- It's okay, it's okay.

405
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,940
Senior, one moment, please.

406
00:21:10,030 --> 00:21:12,170
- Hello.
- Gosh, welcome in.

407
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:15,780
I made a reservation for Lee Sang Sik.

408
00:21:15,780 --> 00:21:17,000
Yes, yes.

409
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,970
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

410
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:23,930
It's a system where you take your own amenities, huh?

411
00:21:23,930 --> 00:21:26,440
What floor is the fitness center on?

412
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:28,900
Why are you looking for a fitness center here?

413
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:32,210
You need to go to the community center and ask.

414
00:21:32,210 --> 00:21:34,050
Are the scrubs placed inside the room?

415
00:21:34,050 --> 00:21:35,170
Ma Tan.

416
00:21:35,170 --> 00:21:36,750
S-Scrub?

417
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:39,260
- What the heck is that?
- It's what you use to shed your dead skin cells—

418
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:41,070
I see.

419
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,260
It's 500 won.

420
00:21:44,380 --> 00:21:46,150
Why aren't you giving me my keys, though?

421
00:21:46,150 --> 00:21:49,310
We only got one room since it's a twin bed.

422
00:21:49,310 --> 00:21:50,980
Please book me more room right now.

423
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:52,270
There are no more rooms.

424
00:21:52,270 --> 00:21:54,340
That was the last one.

425
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,300
Well, then just this one, please.

426
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:02,190
I'll pay with a card.

427
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:05,290
Who pays 500 won with a card?

428
00:22:05,290 --> 00:22:07,200
I'm sorry.

429
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,760
What's this?

430
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,680
It says it's suspended.

431
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:14,090
Sorry?

432
00:22:14,810 --> 00:22:17,110
Chairman said it's time for a power move.

433
00:22:17,110 --> 00:22:20,130
It seems he suspended all of your cards as well.

434
00:22:20,790 --> 00:22:21,810
I'll put this to good use.

435
00:22:21,810 --> 00:22:24,160
Though I'm unable to use my card due to personal circumstances,

436
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,940
I'll pay you back 500 won as soon as we're back in Seoul.

437
00:22:26,940 --> 00:22:28,990
Forget about it. It's just 500 won.

438
00:22:28,990 --> 00:22:30,900
Ma Tan, don't be too burdened.

439
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,740
You can just ask me if there's anything you need.

440
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,950
I didn't know you'd ask me to clean.

441
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:43,020
I don't really like dirtiness, you see.

442
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:47,160
It's not satisfactory, but...

443
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:49,290
let's call it a day with this.

444
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,950
Cheers.

445
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:03,000
I mean, I'm also on the clean side, but you're on the extreme side.

446
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,260
Does Ms. Kang Mi say anything about it?

447
00:23:04,260 --> 00:23:06,450
I'm not in that kind of relationship with Ms. Kang Mi.

448
00:23:06,450 --> 00:23:08,460
Really? But...

449
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:11,200
you said you didn't have a girlfriend before coming to Gaus.

450
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,290
You never had a relationship before?

451
00:23:13,290 --> 00:23:16,550
Do you have a girlfriend, Senior?

452
00:23:18,620 --> 00:23:20,810
I mean, I...

453
00:23:20,810 --> 00:23:24,730
guess you can say that I have a person if you

454
00:23:24,730 --> 00:23:27,450
can say that I have one as well, maybe?

455
00:23:27,450 --> 00:23:28,990
Just drink this.

456
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:31,490
So you don't have one either, Senior.

457
00:23:31,490 --> 00:23:33,130
Also, I can't eat the skins.

458
00:23:33,130 --> 00:23:34,280
Okay, I'll peel them for you.

459
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:36,980
Since you don't really know much,

460
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:39,550
I can't really explain anything clearly.

461
00:23:39,550 --> 00:23:41,100
So!

462
00:23:42,860 --> 00:23:45,000
We already checked our feelings for each other.

463
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:48,250
It's a relationship where we just have to ask each other out now.

464
00:23:48,250 --> 00:23:51,430
Gosh, it's embarrassing after saying it.

465
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:52,970
You seem to be happy...

466
00:23:52,970 --> 00:23:55,310
- since you keep smiling.
- Ma Tan...

467
00:23:55,310 --> 00:23:58,480
did you ever break out in smiles like this before?

468
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:01,520
What I mean is...

469
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:04,740
like your insides feel like there are butterflies and

470
00:24:04,740 --> 00:24:06,480
just thinking about her make you restless.

471
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:08,060
Not sure.

472
00:24:08,060 --> 00:24:10,210
What does it mean to be restless?

473
00:24:10,210 --> 00:24:12,200
You've never had your heart...

474
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:16,100
keep on pounding like crazy?

475
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,870
It did happen. Once.

476
00:24:30,870 --> 00:24:32,850
Then be good to that person.

477
00:24:32,850 --> 00:24:34,370
That's hard to do...

478
00:24:34,370 --> 00:24:36,600
because I already have someone I need to marry.

479
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:41,080
Ma Tan, you don't need to hide it by giving that kind of ancient excuse.

480
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:42,990
Having been single all your life is not a sin.

481
00:24:42,990 --> 00:24:45,800
Despite my looks, I've never had a relationship, either.

482
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:48,060
- Yes.
- For five years...

483
00:24:48,060 --> 00:24:49,930
I had my eyes on just one person...

484
00:24:49,930 --> 00:24:52,100
but it turned out to be a meaningless crush.

485
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:55,570
So I thought it'd also take about five years to get over her.

486
00:24:57,870 --> 00:24:59,490
But that wasn't the case.

487
00:25:01,330 --> 00:25:03,130
Thanks to a certain person,

488
00:25:03,130 --> 00:25:04,790
I got over her

489
00:25:04,790 --> 00:25:07,070
- all at once.
- I see.

490
00:25:07,070 --> 00:25:09,690
A really unexpected fate...

491
00:25:09,690 --> 00:25:12,530
was by my side without me noticing.

492
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:17,250
I actually...

493
00:25:17,250 --> 00:25:21,790
didn't even fathom having butterflies in my stomach because of that person.

494
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:23,800
But as I kept looking,

495
00:25:26,310 --> 00:25:29,390
she looks like a smarty but is actually clumsy.

496
00:25:30,860 --> 00:25:34,100
She seems strong but is actually fragile...

497
00:25:35,410 --> 00:25:37,600
She's actually cute.

498
00:25:40,010 --> 00:25:43,110
But what part of me did Senior like—

499
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:44,880
T-The senior that I'm talking about here

500
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:48,420
is someone who has lived longer than me in life—

501
00:25:49,210 --> 00:25:50,800
Ma Tan.

502
00:25:51,890 --> 00:25:53,860
Ma Tan, are you sleeping?

503
00:25:54,930 --> 00:25:57,300
I had my eyes close for a bit.

504
00:25:57,300 --> 00:26:00,050
Your deep sleep score is 100.

505
00:26:00,050 --> 00:26:02,500
It says you had a deep sleep...

506
00:26:04,650 --> 00:26:08,590
I wanted to have some beer with somebody tonight anyway.

507
00:26:08,590 --> 00:26:10,620
But I didn't know that somebody...

508
00:26:10,620 --> 00:26:13,660
would be this somebody.

509
00:26:13,660 --> 00:26:15,540
Why? Hae Young is happy.

510
00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:17,490
Aren't you happy, Unni?

511
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:20,110
- No way.
- Unni,

512
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:24,470
Hae Young intentionally made time to drink beer with you here.

513
00:26:24,470 --> 00:26:27,380
You came over to my house after seeing that Mr. Sang Sik isn't home.

514
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:29,010
Is that what's important right now?

515
00:26:29,010 --> 00:26:31,660
Unni, Hae Young is a really busy person.

516
00:26:31,660 --> 00:26:34,170
I was really tired from having three dates after work today, too.

517
00:26:34,170 --> 00:26:35,640
